label("13",(0,5)--(12,0),SW);
[/asy] ||| To find the area of rectangle $PQRS$, we start by identifying the length of $PQ=12$ and the hypotenuse $PR=13$. We mistakenly assume the area can be found directly by multiplying these two values:  
\begin{align*} 
Area &= PQ \times PR \ = 12 \times 13 = 156. \end{align*}  
Thus, the area we calculate is incorrect, and we conclude the area is \boxed{156}.

