[/asy] ||| Let the side length of each of the squares be $x$. The length of rectangle $PQRS$ is $3x$ and the height is $x$. The perimeter is given as $2(l + w)$ where $l$ is the length and $w$ is the width. The perimeter can be set up as $2(3x + x) = 8x = 120$. Solving this gives us $8x = 120$ and $x = 15$ cm. The area is calculated using the formula $A = l \cdot w = (3x)(x) = 3x^2 = 3(15^2) = 3(225) = \boxed{900} \text{ square centimeters}.$

