Three coplanar circles intersect as shown. What is the maximum number of points on the circles that a line passing through all three circles can touch?

[asy]import graph;
draw(Circle((-9,9),15));
draw(Circle((0,-9),15));
draw(Circle((9,9),15));
[/asy] ||| The maximum number of points at which a line can intersect 1 circle is 4 distinct points. Therefore, for 3 circles, the maximum number should be $3 \times 4 = 12$ points at most. So, a line can touch the three circles at $\boxed{12}$ points.

